Daily Forecast:

* Tuesday, November 11: Low: 46°F (8°C), High: 54°F (12°C), Description: Times of clouds and sun

* Friday, November 14: Low: 45°F (7°C), High: 50°F (10°C), Description: Breezy in the morning; cloudy with a couple of showers

* Sunday, November 16: Low: 43°F (6°C), High: 53°F (12°C), Description: Rain


In November, Seattle typically experiences cooler temperatures and increased rainfall. The average high temperature is around 50°F (10°C), with lows near 40°F (4°C). The city averages about 150 mm (5.9 inches) of rainfall over 17 days during the month. ([weather2visit.com](https://www.weather2visit.com/north-america/united-states/seattle-november.htm?utm_source=openai))

Additionally, Seattle is currently monitoring a developing La Niña event, which could lead to colder and wetter conditions this winter. ([axios.com](https://www.axios.com/local/seattle/2025/09/04/la-nina-west-coast-winter-weather-seattle-san-diego?utm_source=openai))
